  "text": "For morphometric analysis of H&E stained sections, digital photomicrographs were captured to measure the area and the equivalent diameter of hepatocytes' nuclei under 40× (pixel size, 0.24 μm/pixel). One randomly chosen section of each sample, incorporating both right and left lateral lobes, and ten randomly chosen fields/sections were considered for measurement, so that a minimum of fifty hepatocytes per sample were measured [CITATION_1] . Heptatocytes with a prominent nucleolus within the nucleus were considered for measurement [CITATION_2] . A standard rectangular grid (270×80 μm 2 ) was placed on the section and the uninucleate and binucleate hepatocytes within the measured grid area were counted ( Fig.  2A) . Cells contacting the left and the lower margins of the grid were not counted.",
